  <brief_title>Dose-Exposure-Response in Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus</brief_title>
  <official_title>Dose-Exposure-Response Relationship of Insulin Glulisine (HMR1964) in Subjects With Type 1 Diabetes Mellitus Assessed With the Euglycemic Clamp Technique Using the Biostator (TM)</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Sanofi</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Sanofi</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To investigate the dose-exposure-response relationship of insulin glulisine (HMR1964) after
      single subcutaneous injections of 0.075, 0.15 and 0.3 U/kg body weight with the euglycaemic
      clamp technique using the Biostator (TM).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
